{"title":"Ari Wire Peak v2 eMTB gets More Travel, Bigger Power & Lower Prices","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2024-ari-wire-peak-emtb/","date":1710352800000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-2-800x533.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" alt=\"ari wire peak v2 trail all mountain e-MTB shown climbing a rock\" /></p>\n<p>The second bike coming out under <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/fezzari-changes-to-ari-bikes/\">Fezzari’s updated brand</a>, the new Ari Wire Peak v2 builds on their original all-mountain eMTB by giving it more travel, a bigger battery, the latest Shimano drive systems, and more aggressive angles.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3.jpg\" alt=\"ari wire peak v2 trail all mountain e-MTB shown climbing jumping down singletrack\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Starting with the power, the Wire Peak now has 635Wh battery pack fueling Shimano E7000 or EP801 motors, depending on model.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1638\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-4.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of 2024 ari wire peak e-MTB\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-4.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-4-297x238.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-4-800x640.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-4-120x96.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-4-768x614.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-4-1536x1229.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-10.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"640\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-10-800x640.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of 2024 ari wire peak e-MTB\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-10-800x640.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-10-297x238.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-10-120x96.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-10-768x614.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-10-1536x1229.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-10.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-7.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"640\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-7-800x640.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of 2024 ari wire peak e-MTB\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-7-800x640.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-7-297x238.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-7-120x96.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-7-768x614.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-7-1536x1229.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-7.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The battery is easily removable for riders who want to carry a spare. It’s mounted on their internal rail system, which provides cable, wire, and hose management to keep everything quiet inside.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-9.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1638\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-9.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of 2024 ari wire peak e-MTB\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-9.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-9-297x238.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-9-800x640.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-9-120x96.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-9-768x614.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-9-1536x1229.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1638\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-6.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of 2024 ari wire peak e-MTB\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-6.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-6-297x238.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-6-800x640.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-6-120x96.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-6-768x614.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-6-1536x1229.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The frame is aluminum and has 145mm rear wheel travel paired with 160mm forks. Builds include suspension bits from Rockshox, DVO, and Fox.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-8.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1103\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-8.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of 2024 ari wire peak e-MTB\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-8.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-8-297x160.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-8-800x431.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-8-120x65.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-8-768x414.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-eMTB-Details-8-1536x827.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Increased reach (30mm average across frame sizes) pairs with a slacker 65º head angle for better control on the descents. The seat tube is steeper at 78º, giving the Wire Peak the brand’s signature upright riding position on the climbs. Straight seat tubes and low standover allow for long droppers to get the saddle out of the way on descents.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>2024 Ari Wire Peak Pricing &amp; Specs</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3.jpg\" alt=\"ari wire peak v2 trail all mountain e-MTB shown climbing jumping down singletrack\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-action-3-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Wire Peak Comp – $3799</strong> (<em>Introductory price at $3499</em>)<br />RockShox Recon Silver RL/X-Fusion O2 Pro, SRAM SX Drivetrain, TRP Slate EVO Brakes, Shimano E7000 Drive Unit/635Wh Removable Battery, WTB i30 E-MTB Wheelset</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"459\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-2-800x459.jpg\" alt=\"2024 ari wire peak elite eMTB shown in red color\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-2-800x459.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-2-297x170.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-2-120x69.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-2-768x441.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-2-1536x881.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-2-2048x1175.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"461\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-1-800x461.jpg\" alt=\"2024 ari wire peak elite eMTB shown in tan gray color\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-1-800x461.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-1-297x171.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-1-120x69.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-1-768x442.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-1-1536x885.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ari-Wire-Peak-elite-e-mountain-bike-2024-1-2048x1179.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Wire Peak Elite – $4799</strong><br />DVO Diamond E3l/Opal HV T3, Shimano SLX Drivetrain, SRAM DB8 Brakes, Shimano EP800 Drive Unit/635Wh Removable Battery, Stans Flow S1 E-MTB Wheelset, TransX Travel Adjustable Dropper Post</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Wire Peak Pro – $5799</strong><br />Fox 36 Performance Elite/Float X Performance Elite, Shimano XT Linkglide 11-Speed Drivetrain, TRP Trail EVO Brakes, Shimano EP600 Drive Unit/635Wh Removable Battery, DT Swiss H1900 E-MTB Wheelset, TransX Travel Adjustable Dropper Post</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Available now, all three models come with a lifetime warranty on the frame.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.aribikes.com\" target=\"_blank\">AriBikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2024-ari-wire-peak-emtb/\">Ari Wire Peak v2 eMTB gets More Travel, Bigger Power &amp; Lower Prices</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"2724ae2d6906af1c8c7082384af154101043bcf4c4daaaf3416b568eb7fa70dc","category":"Cycling"}